{"title":"All-new KASK Elemento Aero Helmet Could Be The One For All Disciplines","link":"https://bikerumor.com/all-new-kask-elemento-helmet/","date":1684310400000,"content":"<p>KASK’s new aero road helmet has been hiding in plain sight for months. We’ve seen it protecting the heads of the INEOS Grenadiers on the road and, most recently, Pauline Ferrand-Prevot racing XC mountain bikes at the Nové Město na Moravě World Cup this past weekend.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-34-.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-34--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"KASK Elemento Helmet 3:4\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-34--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-34--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-34--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-34--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-34-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>One thing is for sure; this new helmet is an all-rounder that has already proven effective in many different cycling disciplines. Aero road isn’t just for on-road anymore. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>KASK Elemento aero road bike helmet</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front--800x500.jpeg\" alt=\"KASK Elemento Helmet front\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front--800x500.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front--297x186.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front--120x75.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front--768x480.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This all-new KASK Elemento is a top-tier offering from the Italian helmet manufacturer. A design which aims to help make elite athletes faster competing in the world’s best road, cross-country, cyclocross, and gravel events. To phrase it simply — any cyclist who is driven by the quest for ultimate speed $ performance.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Elemento Development</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front-side.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"467\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front-side-800x467.jpeg\" alt=\"KASK Elemento Helmet front side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front-side-800x467.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front-side-297x173.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front-side-120x70.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front-side-768x448.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front-side.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>KASK started the journey of the Elemento back in 2020, when they conducted an in-depth analysis of numerous scientific studies on how athletes’ performances varied as their body temperatures changed. The study illuminated that an athlete’s thermal comfort (helmet-wise) is as essential as a helmet’s weight and aerodynamics.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>INEOS Grenadiers Testing and Design</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Kask-Elemento-Pauline-Ferrand-Prevot-Nove-Mesto_XCO.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Kask-Elemento-Pauline-Ferrand-Prevot-Nove-Mesto_XCO-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"KASK Elemento aero road helmet, Pauline Ferrand-Prevot INEOS XCO Nove Mesto\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Kask-Elemento-Pauline-Ferrand-Prevot-Nove-Mesto_XCO-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Kask-Elemento-Pauline-Ferrand-Prevot-Nove-Mesto_XCO-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Kask-Elemento-Pauline-Ferrand-Prevot-Nove-Mesto_XCO-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Kask-Elemento-Pauline-Ferrand-Prevot-Nove-Mesto_XCO-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Kask-Elemento-Pauline-Ferrand-Prevot-Nove-Mesto_XCO-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Kask-Elemento-Pauline-Ferrand-Prevot-Nove-Mesto_XCO.jpg 1800w\" /></a><figcaption><em>XCO photos by Cory Benson, copyright Bikerumor.com</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>KASK immediately began working with INEOS Grenadiers on the Elemento, across all racing disciplines.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front-close.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"503\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front-close-800x503.jpeg\" alt=\"KASK Elemento Helmet front close\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front-close-800x503.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front-close-297x187.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front-close-120x75.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front-close-768x482.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-front-close.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The INEOS Grenadiers squad and the KASK design team looked to produce a helmet that was not only super aerodynamic but also offered high levels of safety and improved ventilation. A helmet that fits great and does everything well…easy, right?</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Elemento Fluid Carbon 12</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-carbon-back--e1684289145523.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"507\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-carbon-back--e1684289145523-800x507.jpeg\" alt=\"KASK Elemento Helmet carbon back\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-carbon-back--e1684289145523-800x507.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-carbon-back--e1684289145523-297x188.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-carbon-back--e1684289145523-120x76.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-carbon-back--e1684289145523-768x487.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-carbon-back--e1684289145523.jpeg 1110w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Fluid Carbon 12 is a new KASK composite technopolymer capable of absorbing more energy from an impact than traditional materials. The material of the Fluid Carbon 12 shell absorbs the impact and then can distribute that force more evenly across the helmet.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-carbon-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-carbon--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"KASK Elemento Helmet carbon\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-carbon--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-carbon--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-carbon--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-carbon--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-carbon-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>With this new technology, the design team at KASK can increase the size of the Elementos internal channels without worrying about neglecting safety. Increasing the internal vents improves the helmet’s ventilation while simultaneously reducing the size of the ventilation holes, which also makes the helmet more slippery in the wind.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3D-Printed Multipod Technologies</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-padding-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-padding--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"KASK Elemento Helmet padding\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-padding--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-padding--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-padding--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-padding--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-padding-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Multipod is a new KASK-designed structure that is 3D-printed and used for the Elemento’s internal padding. Think of it as an elastomer-like material with more airflow and comfort – just like we’ve seen with 3D-printed saddle padding. These Multipods are a direct result of KASK’s own Rotational Impact WG11 Testing. The WG11 is the internally-developed test protocol performed at KASK to address non-linear impact forces on a rider in a crash. After many tests, KASK found their new Multipods enable the helmet to withstand linear and rotational impacts better. The Multipod structure also has isotropic properties, meaning it’s equally strong in all directions, the same thing that makes 3D-printed saddles so popular.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-3d-printed-padding-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"426\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-3d-printed-padding--800x426.jpeg\" alt=\"KASK Elemento Helmet 3d printed padding\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-3d-printed-padding--800x426.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-3d-printed-padding--297x158.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-3d-printed-padding--120x64.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-3d-printed-padding--768x409.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-3d-printed-padding-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>That characteristic property helped the new Elemento receive a five-star review from Virginia Tech’s highly authoritative test lap.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Octofit+ and No More Leather Strap</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-strap-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-strap--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"KASK Elemento Helmet strap\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-strap--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-strap--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-strap--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-strap--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-strap-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>KASK’s new helmet fit and adjustment system is now dubbed OCTOFIT+, offering easy on-the-fly adjustments and sturdy attachment to the rider’s head.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-retention-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"520\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-retention--800x520.jpeg\" alt=\"KASK Elemento Helmet retention\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-retention--800x520.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-retention--297x193.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-retention--120x78.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-retention--768x499.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-retention-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Elemento also uses the KASKs “Pro” chinstrap, the same ultra-lightweight chinstrap used by INEOS. Bidding arrivederci to the iconic leather strap, that has been a main stay on KASK helmets for years.  </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-side-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"516\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-side--800x516.jpeg\" alt=\"KASK Elemento Helmet side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-side--800x516.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-side--297x192.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-side--120x77.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-side--768x496.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-side-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>KASK Elemento Details</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Sizes:</strong> SM (50 – 56), <strong>MED (52 – 58)</strong>*, LRG (59 – 62) *tested</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Weight: </strong>260 grams (size M)</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Colors: </strong>Classic Black or White, New metallic finishes: Beetle Green, Oxford Blue (pictured), Red, and Silver.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Price: </strong>USD $400, EUR 375€, GBP £335.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>KASK Elemento — Initial Thoughts</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ve had very little time in the KASK Elemento, but what we tell so far is that it is exceedingly comfortable. The helmet disappears on your head, especially when the wind cuts through it on the open road.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-jordan-Villella-close-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-jordan-Villella-close--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"KASK Elemento Helmet jordan Villella close\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-jordan-Villella-close--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-jordan-Villella-close--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-jordan-Villella-close--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-jordan-Villella-close--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-jordan-Villella-close-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The styling and fit are what you would expect from KASK, and the updated metallic color is excellent. The shape is refined enough to keep it out of overly aero-offputting designs and into the good-looking all-around territory. Paired next to the matte Fluid Carbon 12, the shell has a powder-coated look with a deep rich color — very nice.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-side-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"516\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-side--800x516.jpeg\" alt=\"KASK Elemento Helmet side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-side--800x516.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-side--297x192.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-side--120x77.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-side--768x496.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-side-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The helmet is straight-up breezy in the wind, with zero to no wind chatter or slight whistly noises that can accompany some aero helmets.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-jordan-Villella-smile-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-jordan-Villella-smile--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"KASK Elemento Helmet jordan Villella smile\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-jordan-Villella-smile--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-jordan-Villella-smile--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-jordan-Villella-smile--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-jordan-Villella-smile--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/KASK-Elemento-Helmet-jordan-Villella-smile-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>We look forward to more rides in the new KASK Elemento, especially as the summer heat starts. Stay tuned for a full review coming shortly.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.kask.com/en/\" target=\"_blank\">KASK.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/all-new-kask-elemento-helmet/\">All-new KASK Elemento Aero Helmet Could Be The One For All Disciplines</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"36445fd7185eeda90d6dc64d3d27c8ca6536f0917a50890b5d8c3ac8a439b5d9","category":"Cycling"}